<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-02-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="671" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 11513/2.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Bryan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-02-04"><hi rend="italic">February 4,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bryan reports having expressed to the Queen Dowager the sympathy of
                            the President and says the funeral obsequies will occur next Saturday.
                            States that the Prince of Wales and other special ambassadors will
                            attend.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>